\widowctrl\hyphauto

{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 This is will delete everything from the edit cursor to the end of the item.\par}
}

{\rtf1\ansi\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0 \fswiss Helvetica;}{\f1 \fmodern Courier;}}
{\colortbl;\red255\green0\blue0;\red0\green0\blue255;}
\widowctrl\hyphauto

{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 This will remove the item(s) that are selected without affecting any other items or tracks regarless of the ripple editing state. It's great for interviews where there are short items on the non-speaking tracks that you want to remove without accidently cutting audio from the speaker.\par}
}

{\rtf1\ansi\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0 \fswiss Helvetica;}{\f1 \fmodern Courier;}}
{\colortbl;\red255\green0\blue0;\red0\green0\blue255;}
\widowctrl\hyphauto

{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 This will set the volume of the audio within the time selection to -10db. This is great for dealing with really loud breaths. If you don't have any time selection but do have an item selected then it will set that item to -10db. If you have no time selection or items selected then the script does nothing. You don't have to stop playback at all. It will catch back up to the play cursor so that you don't interrupt your listening.\par}
}

{\rtf1\ansi\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0 \fswiss Helvetica;}{\f1 \fmodern Courier;}}
{\colortbl;\red255\green0\blue0;\red0\green0\blue255;}
\widowctrl\hyphauto

{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 You can easily toggle your playrate back and forth for faster editing. You can toggle whether or not you are currently playing audio. It will keep playing if you are currently playing audio but won't start playing if it's paused or stopped.\par}
}
